this API Document Organization

this API (Application Programming Interface) document contains pages corresponding to items in the navigation bar, is described below.

  • Overview

    Overview pages is this API Documentation Home, provides a list of all packages and their summary. This page may also contain general descriptions of these packages.

  • packages

    Each package has a page, It contains a list of its classes and interfaces and a summary of them. This page can contain six categories:

    • interface (Italic)
    • types
    • enums
    • Abnormal error
    • error
    • annotation type

  • types/interface

    per class, interface, Nested classes and nested interfaces each have their own pages. Each of these pages consists of three sections (types/interface description, ​​Summary Table, and detailed member description) Composition:

    • Class Inheritance Graph
    • Direct Subclass
    • all known sub-interfaces
    • all known implementation classes
    • types/Interface declaration
    • types/interface description
    • Nested Class Overview
    • Field Summary
    • Constructor Overview
    • Method summary
    • Field Details
    • Constructor Details
    • Method Details

    Each summary entry contains the first sentence of a detailed description of the item. Summary entries in alphabetical order, The detailed instructions are in the order in which they appear in the source code. This preserves the logical groupings established by the programmer.

  • annotation type

    Each annotation type has its own page, contains the following sections:

    • Annotation Type Declaration
    • annotation type description
    • Essential Elements Summary
    • Summary of Optional Elements
    • Element Details

  • enums

    Each enum has its own page, contains the following sections:

    • enum declaration
    • enum description
    • Enum Constant Summary
    • Enum Constant Details

  • Tree (types of hierarchy)

    for all packages, There istypes of hierarchypages, and the hierarchical structure of each package. Each hierarchy page contains a list of classes and a list of interfaces. Fromjava.lang.ObjectFrom, Arranges classes by inheritance structure. Interface does not followjava.lang.Objectinheritance.

    • When viewing the Overview page, Click "Tree" will show the hierarchy of all packages.
    • View specific packages, class or interface page, Click "Tree" will only show the hierarchy of the package.

  • Obsolete API

    Obsolete API page lists all obsolete APIGenerally due to improvements and often alternatives API, So it is recommended not to use outdated APIIn future implementations, may delete obsolete API.

  • Index

    Index contains all classes in alphabetical order, interface, Constructor, List of methods and fields.

  • previous/next

    These links allow you to go to the next or previous class, interface, package or related page.

  • Frame/no frame

    These links are used to show and hide HTML frame. All pages have both framed and frameless display modes.

  • All classes

    All classeslink showing all classes and interfaces (except for non-static nested types).

  • Serialized Form

    Each serializable or externalizable class has a description of its serialization fields and methods. This information is useful for reimplementers, while using API The developers were useless. Although there are no links in the navigation bar, but you can get this information by: Go to any serialization class, Then click on the class description "See also" In part "Serialized Form".

  • Constant field value

    Constant field valueThe page lists the static final fields and their values.

This help file applies to the use of standards doclet generated API documents.
